bib_record.title: High-resolution study of 166Er with the (p,t) reaction

free_txt: Q3D spectrograph and a 1 m long cathode strip
FWHM energy resolution of about 5 keV.
Statistical uncertainties are given both for
the energies of the levels and the cross sections.
168Er, with a thickness of 120 ug/cm2 deposited on a
13 ug/cm2 carbon backing. The most important impurities
in the target are 166Er and 167Er, about 1% each.
